## Chapter 12 The Engineers

* No more important relationship than the product manager to the engineers.
* Learn to understand the engineer world, coding principles, design and infrastructure constraints.
* "Your job is to bring this information to your team and then to discuss the various potential solutions to these problems."
* "The morale of the engineers is very much a function of you as the product manager."
* It is good practice for the product designer, product manager and the tech lead work together to create a strong solution.
* There are different types of engineers, some enjoy the product work, others prefer to focus on the tech related problems. It is important for the product manager to understand the different personalities in the team and be able to adjust their communication with that engineer given their personality.
